cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.CL

The paper discusses the design and implementation of a programming language that combines logic and imperative programming paradigms, making it likely to fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The use of logic programming features also suggests a possible fit under the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) category. The paper also discusses the need for lists, which is a common data structure in Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), making these categories also likely candidates.
